{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A request whose signature does not match its body is rejected with a 401 response; the body is not forwarded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is handler-to-queue handoff plus signature validation, not just a pure HMAC helper. MOCK-MISS: a unit test of only `verifySignature` can pass while handler still forwards invalid events. REAL-INFRA/INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess is required; in-process HTTP harness is sufficient, so not System. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no AI model and no agent pipeline. Adversarial critique rejected: not choosing Integration just because feature is multi-module; choosing it because this behavior specifically is about cross-module side effect suppression.","test_description":"Run the webhook handler with real signature-check code and a queue spy/fake in the same process. Send a request with mismatched `X-Signature-256` vs raw body. Assert HTTP 401 and assert enqueue/write method was never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"An event is written to the persistent queue before the HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned to the sender.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an ordering guarantee across modules (HTTP handler and persistent queue), so Unit is too low. REAL-INFRA: can be caught with in-process wiring and local persistence test double or local DB/file-backed queue; no real network/OS primitive is required, so not System. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no AI dependency. Rejection-gate: System considered and rejected because behavior text requires write-before-ack ordering, not real HTTP network effects.","test_description":"Wire handler to the real queue adapter used for persistence in tests (e.g., sqlite/file-backed). Instrument queue write completion. Send webhook and assert `200` is emitted on