":"Start the actual Node HTTP server, create concurrent load with earlier requests that trigger slow downstream work, then send fresh requests and measure real wall-clock latency end-to-end over real HTTP (localhost). Assert each response (or defined percentile) is under 3 seconds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"An event whose ID was already received is not written to the queue a second time.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Deduplication failure appears at state handoff across requests (handler + dedupe store/queue), not a single pure function. Unit-only tests can miss persistence/race interactions. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no required real OS/network/subprocess beyond local module wiring and local DB/file store, so not System. No AI dependency and no agentic sequence.","test_description":"Using handler wired to persistent dedupe/queue store, send two requests with same event ID (including near-simultaneous case). Assert only one queue record/write occurs and second attempt is treated as duplicate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the queue reports it is full, the handler returns 503 with a Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is translation of queue-capacity signal into HTTP response semantics across module boundary. Unit of a mapper function is insufficient if wiring/error propagation is wrong. REAL-INFRA check: can be validated with in-process queue adapter returning `QueueFull`; no real network/subprocess needed, so not System. No LLM dependency.","test_description":"Configure/wire handler with queue implementation (or adapter stub at module boundary) that returns a typed 'full' error. Send webhook and assert